{"sectionId":707,"sectionIdLiteral":"707","humanId":"lesson-289","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"The past is over. It can touch me not.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 289"},"annotation":"W-289","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-289\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"707#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Unless the past is over in my mind, the real world must escape my sight.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>For I am really looking nowhere; seeing but what is not there.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>How can I then perceive the world forgiveness offers?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>This the past was made to hide, for this the world that can be looked on only now.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>It has no past.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>For what can be forgiven but the past, and if it is forgiven it is gone.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"707#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, let me not look upon a past that is not there.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>For You have offered me Your Own replacement, in a present world the past has left untouched and free of sin.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Here is the end of guilt.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And here am I made ready for Your final step.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"707#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Shall I demand that You wait longer for Your Son to find the loveliness You planned to be the end of all his dreams and all his pain?</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Unless